		steps
		-- Download and install node (make sure you have stable version)
			https://nodejs.org/en/download/
			>node -v  // this will print the node version installed on your machine
			>npm  -v // this will print the npm version installed on your machine
	
			Purpose 
				node -- it's a execution engine for javascript file
				npm -- node package manager --to install required libs
		--Download and install Microsoft Visual Studio
			https://code.visualstudio.com/
		 Purpose -- This is the IDE to write the code in structured way
		
		-- install typecript libs	
			>npm install -g typescript@latest
			>tsc -v  //it will print typecript version
			
		Multiple ways to start with Angular Project
		1.Manually -- avoid this
		2.git clone
			steps :
				1. Install git and perform following steps
					--download git and install it 
						https://git-scm.com/download/win
					first of all navigate to required folder
					>git clone https://github.com/angular/quickstart.git
					>npm install  // it will check package.json file and download required dependecies to the local node-modules folder
					>npm start   // it executes the angular project on lite server
					
					
					/*
					
					tsc -p src/ -w   -- this will compile all src folder .ts files and creates and .js files
									tsc -- typecript compiler
									-w -- watch mode  -- as and when there is change in source code(.ts) then it will		
														compile .ts file and creates .js files
														and node enginer -- lite-server will executes
														js files.
					
					
					*/
					
					
					
					
					
					
		3.Command line -- Angular CLI
			>npm install -g angular-cli@latest
			>ng new angular-basics
			>cd angular-basics
			>ng serve
		
	
				
now start with IDE
	 navigate to project folder make sure your at package.json location
	 set environment variable
	Copy this path C:\Program Files\Microsoft VS Code\bin
	and add it into path environmentvaribales
	goto control panel -- top right corner search of env
	-- select System level -- click on environmentvaribales
	and edit path variable and add specified path C:\Program Files\Microsoft VS Code\bin
	
	open fresh command prompt -- to  project folder make sure your at package.json location
	and type >code
	
	this will import the project in VScode
	
	
	x.ts
	tsc x.ts -- x.js
	node--- lite server
				
